    <div class="faq-a" id="can-google-detect-ai-generated-content"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google says it does not penalize AI content as long as the output is helpful, original, and accurate. In practice, the Helpful Content System and core updates have flattened sites publishing thin AI content. The pattern Google detects is low-effort production at scale, not the technology itself. A human-edited hybrid loop produces content that passes those signals.</p></div></div>
